  name: RFari
  title: Radiative forcing due to aerosol–radiation interactions
  lead: The radiative forcing (or radiative effect, if the perturbation is internally generated) of an aerosol perturbation due directly to aerosol–radiation interactions, with all environmental variables rem...
  term *Radiative_forcing_due_to_aerosol_radiation_interactions
    # extend *Aerosol_radiation_interaction

    insert text
      | The radiative forcing (or radiative effect, if the perturbation is internally generated) of an aerosol perturbation due directly to aerosol–radiation interactions, with all environmental variables remaining unaffected. Traditionally known in the literature as the direct aerosol forcing (or effect).



  name: ERFari
  title: Effective radiative forcing due to aerosol-radiation interactions
  lead: The final radiative forcing (or effect) from the aerosol perturbation including the rapid adjustments to the initial change in radiation. These adjustments include changes in cloud caused by the impac...
  term *Effective_radiative_forcing_due_to_aerosol_radiation_interactions
    # extend *Aerosol_radiation_interaction

    insert text
      | The final radiative forcing (or effect) from the aerosol perturbation including the rapid adjustments to the initial change in radiation. These adjustments include changes in cloud caused by the impact of the radiative heating on convective or largerscale atmospheric circulations, traditionally known as semi-direct aerosol forcing (or effect).
      | The total effective radiative forcing due to both aerosol–cloud and aerosol–radiation interactions is denoted aerosol effective radiative forcing (ERFari+aci).


    name: See Also
