  name: Climate feedback
  title: Climate feedback
  lead: An interaction in which a perturbation in one climate quantity causes a change in a second, and the change in the second quantity ultimately leads to an additional change in the first. A negative feed...
  term *Climate_feedback
    # extend Glossary

    insert text
      | An interaction in which a perturbation in one climate quantity causes a change in a second, and the change in the second quantity ultimately leads to an additional change in the first. A negative {Glossary.*Feedback feedback} is one in which the initial perturbation is weakened by the changes it causes; a positive feedback is one in which the initial perturbation is enhanced. In this Assessment Report, a somewhat narrower definition is often used in which the climate quantity that is perturbed is the global mean {Topics.*Surface_Temperature surface temperature}, which in turn causes changes in the global {Topics.*Radiation_Budgets radiation budget}. In either case, the initial perturbation can either be externally forced or arise as part of {Topics.*Climate_Variability internal variability}.


