  name: Climate Feedback Parameter
  title: Climate Feedback Parameter
  lead: A way to quantify the radiative response of the climate system to a global mean surface temperature change induced by a radiative forcing. It varies as the inverse of the effective climate sensitivity...
  term *Climate_Feedback_Parameter
    # extend Glossary

    insert text
      | A way to quantify the radiative response of the climate system to a global mean {Topics.*Surface_Temperature surface temperature} change induced by a {Topics.*Radiative_Forcing radiative forcing}. It varies as the inverse of the effective {Glossary.*Climate_sensitivity climate sensitivity}. Formally, the Climate {Glossary.*Feedback Feedback} Parameter (a; units: W m–2 °C–1) is defined as: a = (ΔQ – ΔF)/ΔT, where Q is the global mean radiative forcing, T is the global mean air {Glossary.*Surface_temperature surface temperature}, F is the heat flux into the ocean and Δ represents a change with respect to an unperturbed climate.



