      | The climate system is the highly complex system consisting of five major components: the {Topics.*Climate_System atmosphere}, the hydrosphere, the {Glossary.*Cryosphere cryosphere}, the lithosphere and the {Glossary.*Biosphere_terrestrial_and_marine biosphere}, and the interactions between them. The climate system evolves in time under the influence of its own internal dynamics and because of {Topics.*Radiative_Forcing external forcings} such as volcanic eruptions, solar variations and {Glossary.*Anthropogenic anthropogenic} forcings such as the changing composition of the {Glossary.*Atmosphere atmosphere} and {Topics.*Land_Use_Change land use change}.



