  name: Ecosystem
  title: Ecosystem
  lead: An ecosystem is a functional unit consisting of living organisms, their non-living environment, and the interactions within and between them. The components included in a given ecosystem and its spati...
  term *Ecosystem
    # extend Glossary

    insert text
      | An ecosystem is a functional unit consisting of living organisms, their non-living environment, and the interactions within and between them. The components included in a given ecosystem and its spatial boundaries depend on the purpose for which the ecosystem is defined: in some cases they are relatively sharp, while in others they are diffuse. {Glossary.*Ecosystem Ecosystem} boundaries can change over time. Ecosystems are nested within other ecosystems, and their scale can range from very small to the entire {Topics.*Climate_System biosphere}. In the current era, most ecosystems either contain people as key organisms, or are influenced by the effects of {Topics.*Human_Influence human activities} in their environment.



