  name: Energy balance
  title: Energy balance
  lead: The difference between the total incoming and total outgoing energy. If this balance is positive, warming occurs; if it is negative, cooling occurs. Averaged over the globe and over long time periods,...
  term *Energy_balance
    # extend Glossary

    insert text
      | The difference between the total incoming and total outgoing energy. If this balance is positive, warming occurs; if it is negative, cooling occurs. Averaged over the globe and over long time periods, this balance must be zero. Because the climate system derives virtually all its energy from the Sun, zero balance implies that, globally, the absorbed {Glossary.*Solar_radiation solar radiation}, that is, {Glossary.*Incoming_solar_radiation incoming solar radiation} minus reflected solar radiation at the top of the {Topics.*Climate_System atmosphere} and outgoing {Glossary.*Longwave_radiation longwave radiation} emitted by the climate system are equal.


