  name: Energy Balance Model
  title: Energy Balance Model
  lead: An energy balance model is a simplified model that analyses the energy budget of the Earth to compute changes in the climate. In its simplest form, there is no explicit spatial dimension and the model...
  term *Energy_Balance_Model
    # extend Glossary

    insert text
      | An {Glossary.*Energy_balance energy balance} model is a simplified model that analyses the {Topics.*Radiation_Budgets energy budget} of the Earth to compute changes in the climate. In its simplest form, there is no explicit spatial dimension and the model then provides an estimate of the changes in globally averaged temperature computed from the changes in radiation. This zero-dimensional energy balance model can be extended to a one-dimensional or two-dimensional model if changes to the {Glossary.*Energy_budget_of_the_Earth energy budget} with respect to latitude, or both latitude and longitude, are explicitly considered.


