  name: Equilibrium and transient climate experiment
  title: Equilibrium and transient climate experiment
  lead: An equilibrium climate experiment is a climate model experiment in which the model is allowed to fully adjust to a change in radiative forcing. Such experiments provide information on the difference b...
  term *Equilibrium_and_transient_climate_experiment
    # extend Glossary

    insert text
      | An equilibrium climate experiment is a {Topics.*Climate_Modelling climate model} experiment in which the model is allowed to fully adjust to a change in {Topics.*Radiative_Forcing radiative forcing}. Such experiments provide information on the difference between the initial and final states of the model, but not on the time-dependent response. If the forcing is allowed to evolve gradually according to a prescribed {Topics.*Emissions emission} scenario, the time-dependent response of a climate model may be analysed. Such an experiment is called a transient climate experiment.


